Nakheel to Start 5-Year Restructuring Plan, Alkhaleej Says

-- B y   T a m a r a   W a l i d
-- 
2011-08-23T04:46:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/nakheel-to-start-5-year-restructuring-plan-alkhaleej-says.html
Nakheel PJSC, the developer of man-
made islands off Dubai’s coast, will start implementing a 5-year
restructuring plan tomorrow, as part of its agreement with trade
and bank creditors,  Alkhaleej  reported today, citing Chairman
Ali Rashed Lootah.  The developer will issue 4.8 billion dirhams ($1.31
billion) in sukuk to trade creditors a day or two after the
implementation begins, as part of the restructuring agreement
for $13 billion of the company’s debt, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tamara Walid in  Abu Dhabi  at 
 twalid@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
